{{Infobox bridge | name = Carroll Street Bridge | image = Carroll Street Bridge retracting vc.jpg | image_size = 300px | caption = Carroll Street Bridge retracting | official_name = | also_known_as = | carries = 1 lane for eastbound one-way vehicle traffic and 2 walkways | crosses = [[Gowanus Canal]] | locale = [[New York City]] ([[Brooklyn]]) | maint = [[New York City Department of Transportation]] | id = | architect = | designer = | engineering = Brooklyn Department of City Works (Robert Van Buren, Chief Engineer; George Ingram, Engineer-in-Charge)<ref name="Landmark">{{cite web |title=Carroll Street Bridge Designation Report |url=http://s-media.nyc.gov/agencies/lpc/lp/1553.pdf |publisher=New York City Landmarks Preservation Commission |accessdate=1 July 2018}}</ref> | design = [[Retractable bridge]] | mainspan = {{convert|63|ft|m|abbr=on}}<ref name="bridgehunter">{{cite web|url=http://bridgehunter.com/ny/kings/2240260|title=Carroll Street Bridge|last=|first=|date=|website=|publisher=Bridgehunter.com|page=|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|accessdate=June 30, 2018}}</ref> | length = {{convert|107|ft|6|in|m|1|abbr=on}}<ref name="bridgehunter"/> | width = {{convert|17.5|ft|m|abbr=on}}<ref name="bridgehunter"/> | clearance_above = | clearance_below = | traffic = 1,142 (2016)<ref name="nycdot16">{{cite web|url=http://www.nyc.gov/html/dot/downloads/pdf/nyc-bridge-traffic-report-2016.pdf|title=New York City Bridge Traffic Volumes|last=|first=|date=2016|website=|publisher=New York City Department of Transportation|page=10|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|accessdate=June 30, 2018}}</ref> | open = {{start date and age|1889}} | closed = | toll = Free | coordinates = {{coord|40.67806|-73.98917|display=title,inline}} }}
The '''Carroll Street Bridge''' is a [[retractable bridge]] in [[New York City]], crossing the [[Gowanus Canal]] in [[Brooklyn]]. It carries a single {{convert|17.5|ft|m|abbr=off}} wide wooden-decked lane for one-way eastbound vehicular traffic and two walkways. It was completed in 1889.<ref name="bridgehunter"/><ref name="dot">{{cite web|url=http://www.nyc.gov/html/dot/html/infrastructure/bridges-gowanus.shtml#carroll|title="Carroll Street Bridge"|publisher="NYC Dept of Transportation"|accessdate=June 30, 2018}}</ref> It is the least-used of the 794 bridges and tunnels operated by the [[New York City Department of Transportation]], with an average of about one thousand crossings each weekday.<ref name="DOTWebsite">{{cite web |title=NYC DOT - Bridge Statistics |url=http://www.nyc.gov/html/dot/html/infrastructure/bridges.shtml |publisher=New York City Department of Transportation |accessdate=2 July 2018}}</ref>
The Carroll Street Bridge is one of four remaining retractable bridges in the [[United States]]. The only other one in New York City is the [[Borden Avenue Bridge]].<ref name=NYTimes>{{cite news|last=Berger|first=Joseph|title=Antique Bridge Closed to Traffic While It’s Open for Repairs|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2013/05/14/nyregion/beloved-tiny-bridge-in-brooklyn-is-opened-for-repairs.html?_r=0|accessdate=1 July 2018|newspaper=New York Times|date=May 13, 2013}}</ref> It was designated a New York City landmark in 1987.<ref name="Landmark"/>
