{{Orphan|date=May 2011}}

'''Dubinin Trough''' ({{coord|67|10|S|80|30|E|source:GNIS|display=inline,title}}) is an [[Trough (geology)|undersea trough]] named for Soviet Captain [[A.I. Dubinin]], leader of the 1957 Antarctic expedition. The name was proposed by Dr. [[G. Agapova]] of the Geological Institute of the [[Russian Academy of Sciences]], and was approved by the [[Advisory Committee for Undersea Features]] in August 1985.<ref name=gnis/>

