{{unreferenced|date=July 2015}}
A '''lick''' is a small watercourse or an [[ephemeral]] stream. It ranks [[hydrology|hydrologically]] between a [[rill]] and a [[stream]].

[[File:Rill at Holford Combe.JPG|thumb|175px|left|Picture of a rill in [[Holford Combe]].]]

[[Image:Marshall-county-indiana-yellow-river.jpg|thumb|175px|Yellow River in [[Marshall County, Indiana|rural Indiana, USA]]. Rivers and streams of this size are often referred to as "creeks."]]

